\newlabel{fig:optiver-base-diag}{{4}{8}{Optiver \texttt {rolling3} base model diagnostics ($k{=}5$). The loss curve (left) shows stable convergence of the universal model. The confusion matrix (right) shows that the zero-shot model does predict all three classes, unlike collapsed models, though stationary is over-predicted relative to true frequencies.\relax }{figure.caption.7}{}}
